annotationA: Schlank, isoform A; Schlank is a member of the Ceramide Synthases family involved in sphingolipid metabolism. It is essential for ceramide synthesis and modulates triacylglycerol levels and transcriptional expression of body fat metabolism regulators
annotationB: Uncharacterized protein, isoform A; Phosphatidate phosphatase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: regulation of establishment of planar polarity; dephosphorylation
